ODE XIII

To the fountain Bandusia. According to authorities dating from the 12th century this fountain was six miles from Venusia, the birthplace of Horace, according to others it was near Horace's Sabine farm where a ‘ Fontagna degli

Oratini ' is still shown ; cf. Ep. 1. 16. 12.
